1
Act, including specifically the notice and agenda, voting, and
1
2
executive session requirements; and
2
3
3. An annual financial audit and a compliance audit of all
3
4
funds of the association in accordance with the auditing standards
4
5
set forth in the Oklahoma Public School Audit Law. In addition, the
5
6
association shall have performance audits conducted of the
6
7
operations of the association. A performance audit shall be
7
8
conducted no later than December 31, 2014, and by December 31 every
8
9
five (5) years thereafter; and
9
10
4. The association’s committee to review hardship waivers
10
11
submitted pursuant to Section 8-103.2 of this title be comprised of:
11
12
a. five parents or legal guardians of students enrolled
12
13
in public high schools in this state, appointed by the
13
14
Governor, the Attorney General, the Superintendent of
14
15
Public Instruction, the President Pro Tempore of the
15
16
Senate, and the Speaker of the House of
16
17
Representatives, and
17
18
b. one parent or legal guardian of a student enrolled in
18
19
a private high school in this state, appointed by the
19
20
Governor.
20
21
